---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Alert from '../../components/Alert.astro';
import Accordion from '../../components/Accordion.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Troubleshooting: DNS Changes Not Taking Effect"
	description="Step-by-step guide to fix DNS filtering issues when changes aren't working. Learn how to flush DNS cache, verify settings, and resolve common problems."
>
	<Breadcrumb />

	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<header class="relative pb-6 border-b-4 border-blue-600 dark:border-blue-500 mb-8">
			<div class="inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mb-4 bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900 text-green-800 dark:text-green-100">Beginner</div>
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 leading-tight">DNS Changes Not Taking Effect</h1>
			<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
				Your DNS filtering isn't working even after changing settings. This guide will help you diagnose and fix the issue.
			</p>
			<div class="flex gap-6 flex-wrap text-base text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
				<span>‚è±Ô∏è Time Required: 10-15 minutes</span>
				<span>üîß Difficulty: Beginner</span>
			</div>
		</header>

		<Alert type="info">
			<strong>Quick Check:</strong> Before diving deep, try restarting your router and device. This resolves 30% of DNS issues immediately.
		</Alert>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Understanding the Problem</h2>
			<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
				When DNS filtering "doesn't work," it usually means one of these situations:
			</p>
			<ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
				<li>You changed DNS settings but can still access blocked sites</li>
				<li>Filtering works on some devices but not others</li>
				<li>Filtering worked initially but stopped</li>
				<li>Changes take forever to apply</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
				This happens because DNS information is cached at multiple levels: router, device, browser, and apps.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Step-by-Step Solution</h2>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">1</span>
					Verify DNS Settings Are Correct
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">First, confirm your DNS servers are actually set correctly:</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">On Router:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Log into your router admin panel (usually 192.168.1.1 or 192.168.0.1)</li>
					<li>Navigate to Internet/WAN settings</li>
					<li>Look for "DNS Server" or "Primary/Secondary DNS"</li>
					<li>Verify the correct filtering DNS addresses are entered</li>
				</ol>

				<div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 my-4 rounded">
					<strong class="block text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 mb-2">Common Filtering DNS Servers:</strong>
					<ul class="ml-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-1">
						<li><strong>OpenDNS FamilyShield:</strong> 208.67.222.123 / 208.67.220.123</li>
						<li><strong>CleanBrowsing Family:</strong> 185.228.168.168 / 185.228.169.168</li>
						<li><strong>Cloudflare Family:</strong> 1.1.1.3 / 1.0.0.3</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">On Windows Device:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Open Settings ‚Üí Network & Internet ‚Üí Advanced network settings</li>
					<li>Click your connection ‚Üí View additional properties</li>
					<li>Check "DNS server assignment"</li>
					<li>Should say "Automatic (DHCP)" if using router DNS</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">On Mac Device:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>System Settings ‚Üí Network ‚Üí Your connection ‚Üí Details</li>
					<li>Click "DNS" tab</li>
					<li>Should be empty or show router IP if using router DNS</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">On iOS Device:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Settings ‚Üí Wi-Fi ‚Üí Tap (i) next to network name</li>
					<li>Scroll to "DNS"</li>
					<li>Should show "Automatic" or router IP if using router DNS</li>
				</ol>

				<Alert type="warning">
					<strong>Important:</strong> If DNS is set on both router AND device, the device setting wins.
					Remove device-level DNS settings to use router filtering.
				</Alert>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">2</span>
					Flush DNS Cache
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Clear cached DNS entries that may be overriding your new settings:</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Windows:</h4>
				<pre class="bg-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-950 text-green-300 p-4 rounded overflow-x-auto my-4"><code>ipconfig /flushdns</code></pre>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Open Command Prompt as Administrator, run the command, and restart your computer.</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Mac:</h4>
				<pre class="bg-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-950 text-green-300 p-4 rounded overflow-x-auto my-4"><code>sudo dscacheutil -flushcache; sudo killall -HUP mDNSResponder</code></pre>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Open Terminal, run the command, enter your password, and restart your Mac.</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">iOS:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Settings ‚Üí General ‚Üí Transfer or Reset iPhone</li>
					<li>Reset ‚Üí Reset Network Settings</li>
					<li>Note: This will forget all Wi-Fi passwords</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Android:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Settings ‚Üí Apps ‚Üí See all apps ‚Üí Show system</li>
					<li>Find "Private DNS Provider"</li>
					<li>Tap "Storage & cache" ‚Üí Clear cache</li>
					<li>Or restart device (easier method)</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Router:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Power off router completely (unplug from power)</li>
					<li>Wait 30 seconds</li>
					<li>Power back on and wait 2-3 minutes for full restart</li>
				</ol>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">3</span>
					Check for DNS Overrides
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Some apps and settings bypass your DNS configuration:</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Disable DNS over HTTPS (DoH):</h4>

				<strong class="block text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">Chrome:</strong>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Settings ‚Üí Privacy and security ‚Üí Security</li>
					<li>Scroll to "Use secure DNS"</li>
					<li>Toggle OFF or select "With your current service provider"</li>
				</ol>

				<strong class="block text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">Firefox:</strong>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Settings ‚Üí Privacy & Security</li>
					<li>Scroll to "DNS over HTTPS"</li>
					<li>Select "Off"</li>
				</ol>

				<strong class="block text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">Edge:</strong>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Settings ‚Üí Privacy, search, and services</li>
					<li>Scroll to "Security"</li>
					<li>Toggle OFF "Use secure DNS"</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Check for VPN or Proxy Apps:</h4>
				<ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>VPN apps bypass your DNS settings entirely</li>
					<li>Uninstall or disable any VPN apps</li>
					<li>On iOS: Settings ‚Üí General ‚Üí VPN & Device Management</li>
					<li>On Android: Settings ‚Üí Network ‚Üí VPN</li>
				</ul>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Mobile Data:</h4>
				<Alert type="info">
					DNS filtering only works on Wi-Fi. Mobile data uses your carrier's DNS servers.
					Use device-level controls (Screen Time, Family Link) for cellular protection.
				</Alert>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">4</span>
					Test DNS Configuration
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Verify your DNS filtering is actually active:</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Method 1: Command Line Test</h4>

				<strong class="block text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">Windows/Mac Terminal:</strong>
				<pre class="bg-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-950 text-green-300 p-4 rounded overflow-x-auto my-4"><code>nslookup example.com</code></pre>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
					Look at the "Address" line at the top. It should show your filtering DNS server
					(e.g., 208.67.222.123 for OpenDNS), NOT your ISP's DNS (e.g., not 8.8.8.8).
				</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Method 2: Web-Based Test</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Visit <strong>https://www.dnsleaktest.com/</strong></li>
					<li>Click "Extended test"</li>
					<li>Check if results show your filtering DNS provider</li>
					<li>Should show "OpenDNS" or "CleanBrowsing," not your ISP</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Method 3: Block Test</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Try visiting a site that should be blocked (e.g., adult content test page)</li>
					<li>OpenDNS users can test with: <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono">internetbadguys.com</code></li>
					<li>Should see a block page, not the actual site</li>
				</ol>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">5</span>
					Advanced Troubleshooting
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">If basic steps didn't work, try these advanced solutions:</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Set Static DNS on Router (Recommended):</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Log into router admin</li>
					<li>Find "Internet" or "WAN" settings</li>
					<li>Change from "Automatic DNS" to "Manual/Static DNS"</li>
					<li>Enter filtering DNS servers</li>
					<li>Save and reboot router</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Disable IPv6 (Temporary Test):</h4>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
					Some routers don't properly pass DNS settings to IPv6. Temporarily disable IPv6 to test:
				</p>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Router settings ‚Üí IPv6 ‚Üí Disable</li>
					<li>Save and reboot</li>
					<li>Test if filtering now works</li>
					<li>If yes, contact your filtering DNS provider about IPv6 support</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Check Firmware Updates:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Router admin ‚Üí Firmware or System</li>
					<li>Check for updates</li>
					<li>Update if available (older firmware has bugs)</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Factory Reset Router (Last Resort):</h4>
				<Alert type="warning">
					This erases all settings. Document your WiFi name, password, and settings first!
				</Alert>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
					<li>Hold router's reset button for 30 seconds</li>
					<li>Router will restart with factory defaults</li>
					<li>Reconfigure everything from scratch</li>
					<li>Apply DNS settings again</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Common Scenarios & Solutions</h2>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mt-6">
				<Accordion title="Filtering works on some devices but not others">
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">This means affected devices have their own DNS settings overriding the router:</p>
					<ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
						<li>Check device DNS settings (see Step 1)</li>
						<li>Remove any custom DNS configurations</li>
						<li>Turn off VPN apps on those devices</li>
						<li>Disable DoH in browsers (see Step 3)</li>
						<li>Restart the affected devices</li>
					</ul>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Filtering worked yesterday but stopped today">
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Something changed. Common causes:</p>
					<ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
						<li><strong>Router firmware auto-updated:</strong> Check DNS settings weren't reset</li>
						<li><strong>ISP modem reset:</strong> Power outage can reset modem, which resets router</li>
						<li><strong>Browser updated:</strong> New browser versions may enable DoH automatically</li>
						<li><strong>Someone changed settings:</strong> Check router admin login history if available</li>
					</ul>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Changes take 24+ hours to apply">
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">DNS propagation shouldn't take more than a few minutes. If it does:</p>
					<ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
						<li>Your DNS cache isn't being flushed properly</li>
						<li>Restart router AND all devices (not just flush cache)</li>
						<li>Check if you have nested routers (modem/router combo + separate router)</li>
						<li>Some ISP modem/router combos cache DNS aggressively - put ISP box in bridge mode</li>
					</ul>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Test shows wrong DNS server">
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">If nslookup or leak tests show your ISP's DNS instead of filtering DNS:</p>
					<ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
						<li>Router isn't actually applying DNS settings (firmware issue)</li>
						<li>ISP modem is overriding router DNS (put modem in bridge mode)</li>
						<li>Device has static DNS set locally (override router)</li>
						<li>Try setting DNS on each device individually as workaround</li>
					</ul>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Router doesn't have manual DNS option">
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Some basic routers don't allow custom DNS. Solutions:</p>
					<ul class="ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
						<li><strong>Best:</strong> Upgrade to a router that supports custom DNS ($50-100)</li>
						<li><strong>Alternative:</strong> Set DNS on each device individually</li>
						<li><strong>Advanced:</strong> Use DNS filtering that provides VPN profiles (NextDNS, CleanBrowsing)</li>
						<li>See our <a href="/guides/router-config" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline">router configuration guide</a> for compatible models</li>
					</ul>
				</Accordion>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Prevention Tips</h2>
			<ul class="list-none ml-0 space-y-2">
				<li class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold">Document your DNS settings (write them down or take screenshots)</li>
				<li class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold">Check DNS configuration monthly to ensure it hasn't reverted</li>
				<li class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold">Subscribe to your filtering provider's status updates for outages</li>
				<li class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold">Set a calendar reminder to test filtering quarterly</li>
				<li class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold">Use monitoring software (Qustodio, Bark) as a backup alert system</li>
				<li class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold">Teach older kids not to change DNS settings without permission</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Still Not Working?</h2>
			<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">If you've tried everything and DNS filtering still isn't working:</p>
			<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
				<li><strong>Contact your filtering provider's support</strong> - they can check if their servers are blocking your requests</li>
				<li><strong>Try a different filtering DNS provider</strong> - some routers have compatibility issues</li>
				<li><strong>Switch to software-based filtering</strong> - install Qustodio or Net Nanny as an alternative</li>
				<li><strong>Consult our <a href="/faq" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline">FAQ section</a></strong> for more troubleshooting tips</li>
				<li><strong>Reach out via our <a href="/contact" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline">contact form</a></strong> with your router model and symptoms</li>
			</ol>
		</section>

		<div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Related Guides</h2>
			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
				<a href="/guides/dns-filtering" class="block p-5 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg hover:border-blue-500 dark:hover:border-blue-400 hover:bg-white dark:hover:bg-gray-700 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-lg">
					<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">DNS Filtering Setup</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-snug">Complete guide to configuring DNS filtering from scratch</p>
				</a>
				<a href="/troubleshooting/slow-internet" class="block p-5 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg hover:border-blue-500 dark:hover:border-blue-400 hover:bg-white dark:hover:bg-gray-700 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-lg">
					<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Slow Internet After Filtering</h3>
